.TH ELEV 7 "2026-04-20" "1.0.0" "elev Security Notes"
.SH NAME
elev \- security model and operational notes
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBelev\fR(1) is a small setuid command runner backed by PAM and a compact policy
language. It is intended to answer the "run this command as another user under a
simple local policy" problem.
.PP
It is not a containment system. If you need process isolation, filesystem view
restrictions, namespaces, seccomp, or broader application sandboxing, use tools
built for that job such as \fBbwrap\fR(1).
.SH SECURITY MODEL
.IP \(bu 3
Policy is read from a root-owned configuration file and rejected if the path or
opened file is insecure.
.IP \(bu 3
Authentication is delegated to PAM.
.IP \(bu 3
The parent process keeps PAM credentials and the PAM session alive while the
command runs, then closes both after the command exits.
.IP \(bu 3
The child process drops privileges, sanitizes the environment, and executes the
target command.
.IP \(bu 3
Authentication persistence is limited to real TTY sessions, stored in a
root-owned runtime directory, and scoped to the target user, matched rule, and
command line. Bare \fBpersist\fR rules default to 5 minutes.
.SH NON-GOALS
.IP \(bu 3
\fBelev\fR does not try to sandbox the program you allowed.
.IP \(bu 3
\fBelev\fR does not make shells, interpreters, editors, pagers, package managers,
or other complex programs "safe" once you permit them.
.IP \(bu 3
\fBdenycmd\fR is not meant to stop deliberate shell tricks or alternate execution
paths. It is a convenience guardrail for policy authors.
.SH POLICY GUIDANCE
.IP \(bu 3
Prefer exact command paths in \fBcmd\fR rules.
.IP \(bu 3
Prefer small allowlists over broad user or group grants.
.IP \(bu 3
Treat \fBnopass\fR as a strong trust decision.
.IP \(bu 3
Use \fBkeepenv\fR sparingly; only \fBTERM\fR, \fBLANG\fR, \fBLANGUAGE\fR, and
\fBLC_\fR locale variables can be preserved.
.IP \(bu 3
Prefer exact command paths in rules. Bare command names at invocation time are
resolved only through \fBelev\fR's fixed secure \fBPATH\fR.
.IP \(bu 3
Do not grant shells or interpreters unless you intend to grant their full power.
.SH OPERATIONS
.IP \(bu 3
Install the binary setuid root and keep the configuration tree owned by root and
unwritable by group or others.
.IP \(bu 3
Review PAM policy in \fI/etc/pam.d/elev\fR for the local platform. Linux,
FreeBSD, NetBSD, OpenBSD, and macOS may require different PAM stack entries.
.IP \(bu 3
Use \fBelev -k\fR to invalidate cached authentication for the current user and TTY.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR elev (1),
.BR elev (5),
.BR bwrap (1),
.BR pam (8)
